    dek: `A handful of camera moves make up almost the entire vocabulary of great aerial cinematography. Learn these five or six cold and you can shoot most of what any drone film needs. More importantly, each move <em>says</em> something — so knowing them isn't just technique, it's learning the language of what a drone shot can express.`,
